The paper discusses the security of wireless sensor networks and intrusion detection systems, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The proposed framework for mitigating sleep deprivation attacks involves clustering and layering, which are concepts commonly studied in the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of simulation and modeling techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
